<docs>
	<doc for="FlagsAttribute.FlagsAttribute">
		<summary>
			<para> Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="System.FlagsAttribute"/> class.
   </para>
		</summary>
	</doc><doc for="FlagsAttribute">
		<summary>
			<para> Indicates that an enumeration can be treated as
      a bit field; that is, a set of flags.</para>
		</summary>
		<remarks>
			<para>Bit fields can be combined using a bitwise OR operation, whereas enumerated constants
      cannot.</para>
			<para>Bit fields are generally used for lists of elements that
      might occur in combination, whereas enumeration constants are generally used for
      lists of mutually exclusive elements. Therefore, bit fields are designed to be
      combined with a bitwise OR operation to generate unnamed values, whereas
      enumerated constants are not. Languages vary in their use of bit fields compared to enumeration
      constants.</para>
			<para><see cref="System.AttributeUsageAttribute"/> is applied to this class, and its
<see cref="System.AttributeUsageAttribute.Inherited"/> property specifies <see langword="false"/>. This attribute 
   can only be applied to enumerations.</para>
		</remarks>
	</doc></docs>
